Aberdeen tickets for two special Scottish League Cup trains go on sale
Hundreds of tickets for two special trains for football fans from Aberdeen heading to the Scottish League Cup Final in Glasgow have gone on sale.ScotRail is running the two trains - for up to 720 fans - on the morning of Sunday 16 March for the game against Inverness.Tickets went on sale at Pittodrie at 09:00.Tickets for two special ScotRail trains from Inverness, providing up to 800 seats, will go on sale on Saturday.